  <original-body>It seems that Rails uses the MiniTest implementation of Test::Unit in some cases, and the standard implementation in others - I haven't been able to work out how that works, but the fact of the matter is: A test in the Action Pack suite fails because it references `Test::Unit::AssertionFailedError` even though it might not exist.

I'm attaching a patch in a minute that changes the test to reference the generic `ActiveSupport::TestCase::Assertion` which changes depending on which `Test::Unit` implementation is used.</original-body>
